@edsantiago okay, I did a massive re-arranging/cleanup of the commits and they flow much better now.  However, I appear to be hitting something related to the https://github.com/containers/buildah/issues/2857 fix:

```level=error msg="The storage 'driver' option must be set in /etc/containers/storage.conf, guarantee proper operation."```

I'm hesitant to put the workaround back given it's age.  Are you aware of another fix?
